<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">ESG: Greenium</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have talked a <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25008175.273683/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMDgvbGVuZGluZy1iaXRjb2lucy1pcy=
10cmlja3k/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdd02f5bc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> couple</a> of <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25008175.273683/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJ=
nLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMDkvdHdlbnR5LXBlcmNlbnQtb2YtYS1waW=
N0dXJlLW9mLWEtZG9n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCa61e1c44" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> times</a> this week=C2=A0about=
 ESG loans, bank loans where companies pay a bit less interest for hitting =
certain environmental, social and governance targets but pay a bit more int=
erest if they miss those targets. One fact about these loans is that the di=
scounts and penalties tend to be small, often one or five basis points eith=
er way.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A different but related form of ESG=
 borrowing is a =E2=80=9Cgreen bond.=E2=80=9D In a green bond, a company bo=
rrows money and commits to use it for some sort of environmental-sustainabi=
lity project; in exchange, the bond carries an interest rate that is lower =
than the company would ordinarily pay. (ESG loans, on the other hand, usual=
ly have no committed use of proceeds, but have higher or lower interest dep=
ending on whether the company does enough green things.) This difference =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0the reduction in the interest rate for doing green stuff =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0is called the =E2=80=9Cgreenium.=E2=80=9D With demand for envir=
onmental sustainability soaring, the greenium=C2=A0is higher now than it ha=
s ever been.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
25008175.273683/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjE=
tMDktMTAvZmF0dGVyLWdyZWVuaXVtLWJlY2tvbnMtc3BhaW4tdG8tb3Jlby1tYWtlci1pbi1lc2=
ctZ29sZGlsb2Nrcw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf6a6212c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Also it is two basis points</a>:<=
/p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There has never been a better t=
ime to sell green bonds in Europe.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A =
boom in ESG investing has pushed up the =E2=80=9Cgreenium=E2=80=9D investor=
s are willing to pay for debt that complies with a set of environmental, so=
cial, and governance criteria, according to Deutsche Bank AG. That=E2=80=99=
s flushed out debut green deals from issuers as diverse as Spain and Oreo-c=
ookie maker Mondelez International Inc.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=
=80=9CWe are now able to go to issuers and tell them =E2=80=98if you issue =
your debt in green format, you will actually save money,=E2=80=99 meaning t=
hat the hurdles we had to overcome for our clients to issue green bonds are=
 now gone,=E2=80=9D said Henrik Johnsson, co-head of investment banking EME=
A at Deutsche Bank in London. =E2=80=9CWe are in a Goldilocks moment.=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CEverything else equa=
l, investors are willing to pay more for a green bond than for a convention=
al bond,=E2=80=9D Pablo de Ramon-Laca, director general of Spain=E2=80=99s =
Treasury said in an interview with Bloomberg TV Wednesday. The government c=
ited an estimate by lead managers on the deal that it achieved a greenium =
=E2=80=9Cof around 2 basis points.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">To be fair, the greenium is sometimes bigger for corporate bo=
rrowers, particularly ones that pay higher rates generally. Except that 39%=
 of the time it apparently isn=E2=80=99t?</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">According to Deutsche Bank research, borrowers of green bonds go=
t a reduced rate vis-a-vis their outstanding debt on 61% of deals sold in t=
he second half of 2020, an increase over the first half.</p></blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/25008175.273683/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDctMDgvc29tZW9uZS1pcy1nb2luZy10by1kcmlsbC10aGUtb2l=
s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3b7a900a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;"> two great narratives of ESG investing</a>: =E2=
=80=9CWe will invest in good-ESG companies rather than bad-ESG companies in=
 order to raise the cost of capital for bad-ESG companies and drive bad ESG=
 practices out of the market, accepting a lower return on investment for ou=
rselves in order to create incentives for companies to do the right thing,=
=E2=80=9D versus =E2=80=9Cwe will invest in good-ESG companies because they=
 will outperform in a future world that cares more about environmental and =
social issues, so we will get a higher return on investment for ourselves.=
=E2=80=9D People kind of hate that first narrative because it=C2=A0<em>requ=
ires them to accept lower returns</em>, and nobody wants that; everyone wou=
ld rather say =E2=80=9Cwe do well while doing good=E2=80=9D instead of =E2=
=80=9Cwe do good by sacrificing some money.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">The greenium, of course, fits with the first narrative: Inv=
estors explicitly accept a lower return on investment[3] in exchange for fi=
nancing good ESG projects and not bad ones. They are willing to pay =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0accept a lower interest rate =E2=80=94=C2=A0for something that mak=
es them feel good. They=E2=80=99re just not willing to pay very much.</p><t=
able class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpad=
ding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">ESG: Recycling</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have been saying for the last <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25008175.273683/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMDgvbGVuZGluZy1=
iaXRjb2lucy1pcy10cmlja3k/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCdd02f5bc" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: n=
one !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bor=
der-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> couple</a> of <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25008175.273683/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMDkvdHdlbnR5LXBlcmN=
lbnQtb2YtYS1waWN0dXJlLW9mLWEtZG9n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cDa61e1c44" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> days</a> that =
=E2=80=9Cthere is probably a lot of value to be created by telling people s=
oothing things about ESG, and in practice, if someone creates=C2=A0that val=
ue, a lot of intermediaries in the chain will capture some of it.=E2=80=9D =
People want to think that their investing dollars go to companies that are =
doing good things on environmental, social and governance metrics, but they=
