=9D according to a statement released by Brown=E2=80=99s office. =E2=80=9CS=
pecial rules address the treatment of foreign corporations,=E2=80=9D though=
 so-called inverted companies -- a term used to describe American firms tha=
t shift their headquarters abroad -- =E2=80=9Care fully subject to the exci=
se tax.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I tend to thi=
nk of stock buybacks and dividends as more or less identical transactions, =
but one important difference between them is that buybacks are more tax-eff=
icient. If a company pays a dividend, every shareholder gets cash and has t=
